# Enable mouse
set -g mouse on

# Status bar
set -g status-style 'fg=white,bg=black'
set -g status-left '[#S] '
set -g status-right ' #H'

# Key bindings
bind-key C-a send-prefix
bind-key '"' split-window -v
bind-key '%' split-window -h

# vi copy mode
set -g mode-keys vi
```

> [!NOTE]
> The composed statusline path already renders `status-left`,
> `window-status-format` window lists, `status-right`, `%...` time formats,
> `status-position`, and `status-interval` from effective session/window state.
> The remaining tmux-parity gap under active review is inline `#[...]` style
> fragments inside those status strings: `status-style` currently applies the
> bar-wide style, but embedded tmux style markers are not yet interpreted as
> per-segment styling.

## Differences from tmux

| Feature | tmux | zmux |
|---------|------|------|
| Language | C | Zig |

